<font color="#D900D9">(ELEVATOR ARRIVAL SOUND)</font>

23:19.515 --> 23:23.656
<font color="#D900D9">(MUSIC CONTINUES)</font>

23:50.443 --> 23:56.086
<font color="#D900D9">(MUSIC FADES)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(PEOPLE MUTTERING, OFFICE NOISE)</font>

24:06.510 --> 24:07.510
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> Need some help?

24:07.638 --> 24:12.118
<font color="#808080">ADAM:</font> Uh, yeah, yeah. I... I'm looking for
a station 15, sector 8.

24:12.473 --> 24:13.621
Third aisle down.

24:14.005 --> 24:15.005
Thank you.

24:17.525 --> 24:20.708
<font color="#D900D9">(PEOPLE CHATTERING)</font>

24:25.866 --> 24:29.700
<font color="#D900D9">(SOFT ORCHESTRAL MUSIC)</font>

24:37.449 --> 24:40.230
<font color="#D900D9">(NO TALK; ONLY WELCOME GESTURE)</font>

24:52.998 --> 24:54.498
"WELCOME"

24:54.604 --> 24:55.725
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> Welcome aboard, newbie!

24:55.728 --> 24:57.168
<font color="#808080">- WOMAN 1:</font> Cheers.<font color="#808080">
- WOMAN 2:</font> Cheers.

25:03.312 --> 25:04.463
<font color="#D900D9">(BEER OOZING)</font>

25:04.563 --> 25:07.389
- Goddammit!
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHTER)</font>

25:07.607 --> 25:10.470
I'm so... so sorry.
I... I... I had no idea...

25:10.588 --> 25:13.688
- I was gonna...<font color="#808080">
BOB:</font> - Don't worry, my friend.

25:13.788 --> 25:15.995
They do that to all the newbies.

25:16.095 --> 25:17.569
Oh, great...

25:18.787 --> 25:21.402
My name's Bob, Bob Boruchowitz.

25:22.136 --> 25:23.638
And you are?

25:23.738 --> 25:26.463
I'm Adam, Adam Kirk.

25:26.563 --> 25:27.697
<font color="#808080">ASSISTANT:</font> Mr. Kirk?

25:28.911 --> 25:32.275
Please, follow me. The managing
director is waiting to see you.

25:32.524 --> 25:35.044
Right, sure, uh.
Okay, thanks.

25:36.618 --> 25:37.824
<font color="#808080">BOB:</font> Psst! Hey, hey!

25:38.475 --> 25:39.540
Your back...

25:40.037 --> 25:41.433
Your back, check it out.

25:43.610 --> 25:44.982
<font color="#808080">ADAM:</font> Oh...

25:45.680 --> 25:49.100
Right... that's, uh...
That's pretty funny.

25:49.200 --> 25:50.218
Oh ho.

25:50.318 --> 25:53.418
<font color="#808080">ASSISTANT:</font> Mr. Kirk,
we don't have much time!

25:55.394 --> 25:56.939
Come see me on your way out

25:57.039 --> 25:59.630
for the list of materials
you require for your work.

25:59.819 --> 26:02.895
I need you to complete
your security clearance form.

26:03.380 --> 26:07.935
I'll also give you your various
access badges and meal vouchers.

26:09.302 --> 26:10.834
<font color="#D900D9">(KNOCKING ON THE DOOR)</font>

26:11.769 --> 26:13.378
<font color="#808080">LAGAVULLAN:</font> Come in, Mr. Kirk.

26:17.200 --> 26:19.010
Come in, come in.

26:22.583 --> 26:26.913
This anti-aging cream idea of yours
seems to be quiet promising.

26:28.132 --> 26:29.918
Your application has been approved.

26:30.628 --> 26:33.385
But this is strictly on a trial basis,
you understand?

26:34.048 --> 26:35.609
O... Of course.

26:36.201 --> 26:37.739
Have a seat, please.

26:38.100 --> 26:39.100
Thanks.

26:40.756 --> 26:42.756
Fasten your seat belt, Mr. Kirk.

26:43.436 --> 26:44.566
I'm sorry?

26:44.666 --> 26:45.637
Your seat belt.

26:45.737 --> 26:48.068
Seat...
Oh, right.

26:50.292 --> 26:52.729
<font color="#D900D9">(SEAT BELT LOCK CLICK)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(MOTOR NOISE)</font>

26:52.829 --> 26:54.847
Are there any questions, Mr. Kirk?

26:56.149 --> 27:00.476
Yeah, I was just wondering what
all these people up my side do?

27:02.041 --> 27:04.419
Mmh...
They're merely adapters.

27:04.951 --> 27:07.152
They adapt our products
to your world.

27:07.463 --> 27:08.595
<font color="#D900D9">(REMOTE CONTROL CLICKING)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(MOTOR NOISE STOPS)</font>

27:09.057 --> 27:11.636
You on the other hand have
a real opportunity here.

27:12.299 --> 27:14.346
Company policy
doesn't normally allow

27:14.452 --> 27:18.297
for someone from... 'down below'
to hold such an important position,

27:18.397 --> 27:21.520
but were making an exception
in your case.

27:22.012 --> 27:24.249
Sign here, please.

27:28.827 --> 27:32.696
<font color="#D900D9">(REMOTE CONTROL CLICKING)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(MOTOR NOISE)</font>

27:40.197 --> 27:43.463
Now then, a word of warning...

27:44.302 --> 27:48.195
We scrupulously observe a full
separation between worlds here.

27:48.775 --> 27:53.128
That means there is to be no
unnecessary contact with those up top.

27:53.496 --> 27:55.685
Just stick to your job
and all will be well.

27:56.229 --> 27:57.602
One last thing...

27:57.945 --> 28:00.062
The rules are quite strict here.

28:00.162 --> 28:02.736
As you know, you'll be working
with upper world materials.

28:02.878 --> 28:05.718
This means that you will be
thoroughly searched and weighed

28:05.824 --> 28:08.072
every time
that you leave the premises.

28:08.487 --> 28:10.983
If they find
any inverse-matter on you,

28:11.083 --> 28:13.858
you'll be fired
and jailed on the spot.

28:15.384 --> 28:19.040
But I have a feeling that
this won't happen in your case,...

28:20.302 --> 28:22.520
will it, Mr. Kirk?

28:24.412 --> 28:25.595
No, sir.

28:26.506 --> 28:28.186
Try not to prove me wrong.

28:31.333 --> 28:34.085
Right then...
Dismissed!

28:34.185 --> 28:35.681
<font color="#D900D9">(WHIRRING MACHINE SOUND)</font>

28:35.948 --> 28:39.650
<font color="#808080">TV VOICE:</font> <i> Another massive oil leak has developed,
following a metal robbery from the main pipeline</i>

28:39.673 --> 28:42.768
<i>forcing TransWorld to
double their security.</i>

28:42.781 --> 28:46.563
<i>The three thieves from down below
arrested last week were hanged</i>

28:46.650 --> 28:49.520
<i>this morning at dawn
raising interworld tensions.</i>

28:49.528 --> 28:52.203
<i>Here's the senior TransWorld
executive with a statement...</i>

28:52.213 --> 28:54.672
<font color="#808080">LAGAVULLAN:</font> <i> They got what they deserved.
We don't go down to their world,</i>

28:54.753 --> 28:57.698
<i>we certainly don't want them coming up to ours.</i>
- Hey.

28:57.148 --> 29:00.548
<i>- That was Mr. Lagavuallan, director of floor zero.</i> <font color="#808080"> PABLO:</font>
- Nice boss you got there.

29:00.563 --> 29:03.870
<i>And that's tonight's news on TTW7.</i>

29:04.142 --> 29:05.396
<i>Thank you for watching us.</i>

29:05.751 --> 29:08.389
<font color="#808080">ALBERT:</font> Adam,
you did not have to do this.

29:08.898 --> 29:10.767
I could have gotten you
that patent.

29:10.969 --> 29:13.950
TransWo... TransWorld is the worst
thing that ever happened to us.

29:14.050 --> 29:15.730
And what now, you're...
you're one of them?

29:15.820 --> 29:16.820
<font color="#808080">ADAM:</font> Come on, Albert...

29:16.920 --> 29:18.884
Those people are vultures.

29:18.984 --> 29:21.534
And you're gonna give them
your golden goose for peanuts?

29:21.830 --> 29:23.131
We have nothing!

29:23.829 --> 29:26.858
Yeah, we're from down below.
I mean, that's just the way it is.

29:26.958 --> 29:28.479
I mean, we have nothing.

29:30.065 --> 29:31.721
Don't you tell me I'm nothing!

29:32.419 --> 29:34.774
This isn't nothing,
this is everything!

29:35.057 --> 29:37.388
And I gave you everything,

29:37.755 --> 29:40.583
treated you like you were
my own son!

29:40.926 --> 29:42.133
And you know what
you're gonna do?

29:42.233 --> 29:44.215
You gonna go out there and
you're gonna get yourself killed!

29:44.315 --> 29:46.868
That's all you're gonna do...
get yourself killed.

29:47.268 --> 29:48.391
Shit...

29:51.204 --> 29:52.293
What?

29:58.280 --> 29:59.829
Al... Albert, come on!

29:59.929 --> 30:01.356
I didn't mean it like that.

30:02.846 --> 30:04.290
<font color="#808080">ADAM:</font> Albert, please, come on!

30:06.420 --> 30:07.420
Alright...

30:07.520 --> 30:09.437
Don't you dare to think
that I have forgotten

30:09.537 --> 30:12.395
that TransWorld took away
my entire family!

30:12.927 --> 30:14.051
Alright?

30:19.742 --> 30:20.742
Look...

30:21.978 --> 30:24.238
If I could use TransWorld...

30:24.924 --> 30:27.870
and... and aunt Becky's
pink powder just to...

30:27.970 --> 30:29.148
I... I... I don't know...

30:29.248 --> 30:31.289
Just to give my life
some kind of hope.

30:33.384 --> 30:34.957
That's how I'm gonna do it.

30:36.069 --> 30:37.702
Come on, Albert, please!

30:40.908 --> 30:43.050
Come on, I need you your help.

30:43.263 --> 30:44.505
Albert, please!

30:45.191 --> 30:46.540
Come on!

30:49.498 --> 30:50.498
<font color="#D900D9">(EXHALES)</font>

30:51.498 --> 30:53.970
Alright...
Alright, I'll help.

31:01.199 --> 31:04.370
<font color="#D900D9">(SOFT TUNE FADES IN)</font>

31:05.405 --> 31:06.405
<font color="#808080">PSYCHOLOGIST:</font> Okay...

31:07.186 --> 31:10.007
Today we have someone joining us
for the first time.

31:10.107 --> 31:11.753
Hello, Eden.

31:11.853 --> 31:12.853
<font color="#808080">EDEN:</font> Hi.

31:12.953 --> 31:14.615
<font color="#D900D9">(GROUP RESPONDS)</font> Hi.

31:14.900 --> 31:16.983
Eden. Eden Moore.

31:17.621 --> 31:18.745
Uhm...

31:18.845 --> 31:21.195
I had an accident
when I was a teenager.

31:22.336 --> 31:23.336
Uhm...

31:23.436 --> 31:25.395
Everything before that is gone.

31:26.258 --> 31:29.512
Sometimes things come
back to me in dreams.

31:30.187 --> 31:34.434
But I'm never sure if they're real
or if I'm making them up.

31:35.866 --> 31:37.155
It's frustrating.

31:37.255 --> 31:38.883
You know, I...

31:38.983 --> 31:41.912
I know that whatever is missing,
it's in there.

31:43.651 --> 31:44.680
Uhm...

31:44.780 --> 31:46.597
But it scares me.

31:47.236 --> 31:48.561
Uhm...

31:49.294 --> 31:52.205
Mostly it just feels like
something's missing.

31:52.844 --> 31:54.642
Mr. Kirk?

31:54.742 --> 31:55.746
Yes.

31:55.846 --> 31:59.647
Here's the key to your
personal refrigeration system.

31:59.747 --> 32:00.572
<font color="#D900D9">(BEEP)</font>

32:01.019 --> 32:05.172
And here's your very first allocation...

32:07.065 --> 32:08.528
of inverse-matter.

32:08.757 --> 32:09.757
Okay, great.

32:09.857 --> 32:12.650
Be careful. Without cooling
it gets hot very fast.

32:12.886 --> 32:13.886
Err...

32:15.880 --> 32:16.992
Thank you.

32:18.495 --> 32:22.056
<font color="#808080">BOB:</font> Hey...
Not exactly a charmer, is he?

32:23.689 --> 32:25.020
<font color="#D900D9">(BUZZER RINGS)</font>
- Oh!

32:25.274 --> 32:27.096
<font color="#808080">- MAN 1:</font> Lunch time.<font color="#808080">
- MAN 2:</font> Lunch time!

32:27.411 --> 32:30.220
I usually go to the smoking room
after lunch break.

32:30.740 --> 32:34.727
Why don't you drop by,
and we have a little conversation?

32:36.171 --> 32:37.614
Okay, sure.

32:37.874 --> 32:42.016
<font color="#D900D9">(FUTURISTIC TUNE)</font>

32:48.038 --> 32:49.327
<font color="#808080">ADAM:</font> - Hey, Bob?<font color="#808080">
BOB:</font> - Mmh?

32:49.427 --> 32:51.516
Mind if I come in?

32:51.658 --> 32:53.705
Come in, come in,
sit down, hey!

32:53.906 --> 32:54.959
Want a cigar?

32:55.059 --> 32:57.172
- Smoke?
- No, no, thanks. I don't smoke.

32:57.420 --> 32:58.804
Okay, fine.

33:01.324 --> 33:06.400
<font color="#D900D9">(SOFT ELECTRONIC TUNE)</font>

33:08.778 --> 33:11.464
See? Empty.

33:12.766 --> 33:16.185
<font color="#D900D9">(IMITATING PA VOICE)</font> "No one smokes in
TransWorld anymore..." pfft.. Well, I do so.

33:16.285 --> 33:19.261
<font color="#D900D9">(BOTH LAUGHING)</font>

33:19.711 --> 33:23.933
Hell, people have a funny way
of seeing things here.

33:24.455 --> 33:27.922
Anything or anyone different is...

33:28.383 --> 33:29.566
well, they say...

33:29.815 --> 33:31.116
'frowned upon'.

33:33.435 --> 33:35.044
Can I ask you a favor?

33:36.866 --> 33:37.919
<font color="#808080">ADAM:</font> Yeah.

33:38.019 --> 33:39.019
Yeah, sure.

33:47.361 --> 33:49.479
Can you get me some stamps?

33:50.368 --> 33:52.472
Some stamps?

33:53.265 --> 33:55.655
Yeah... stamps.

33:56.483 --> 33:57.524
I, uh...

33:57.624 --> 33:59.329
I don't like to boast, but...

33:59.429 --> 34:03.463
I got one of the largest known
stamp collections up top.

34:04.031 --> 34:06.895
And if you can get
me some from your side...

34:07.178 --> 34:08.918
Oh, boy...!

34:09.994 --> 34:11.864
Right, yeah, I mean, uh,...

34:12.047 --> 34:13.987
I mean... sure, I guess.

34:14.088 --> 34:16.541
Great... Great!

34:17.353 --> 34:18.690
So, you're saying...

34:18.927 --> 34:20.406
anti-gravity...

34:20.831 --> 34:22.844
Yeah, you know, I... I've...

34:22.944 --> 34:24.677
Well,
I've been working on this, uh...

34:25.091 --> 34:27.989
- Well, it's an anti-aging cream.
- Uhum.

34:28.391 --> 34:30.208
Oh... well,
I'm here if you need me,

34:30.309 --> 34:32.438
expert in conductivity,
in computer programming,

34:32.539 --> 34:34.817
anything you need, anything,
just ask.

34:34.917 --> 34:36.308
<font color="#D900D9">(BOB SMIRKING)</font>

34:36.768 --> 34:37.987
Well, then, uh...

34:38.627 --> 34:41.311
I... I... I guess there could be
something you could help me with...

34:41.411 --> 34:42.436
uhm...

34:43.596 --> 34:47.417
I was wondering if you might be able
to get me in touch with an employee...

34:48.766 --> 34:50.197
...up top.

34:51.783 --> 34:52.789
Up top?

34:52.889 --> 34:53.889
Yeah.

34:54.846 --> 34:56.764
Her name's, uh...

34:58.125 --> 34:59.415
Eden Moore.

35:02.337 --> 35:04.064
Sure...

35:06.123 --> 35:07.164
Sure.

35:19.904 --> 35:22.353
<font color="#D900D9">(METALLIC NOISE OF BICYCLES)</font>

35:25.926 --> 35:29.026
<font color="#D900D9">(CITY NOISE)</font>

35:30.520 --> 35:32.966
<font color="#808080">ALBERT:</font> So, what's your plan?

35:34.504 --> 35:36.610
<font color="#808080">ADAM:</font> I don't know yet.

35:37.627 --> 35:38.881
Working on it.

35:40.171 --> 35:42.490
<font color="#808080">PABLO:</font> I mean,
but you've seen her, alright?

35:43.697 --> 35:46.536
No, I mean...
I... I haven't actually seen her, but...

35:47.376 --> 35:51.781
...but she's there, Pablo. I mean,
she's just like a... fifth floors above.

35:56.428 --> 35:58.190
Are you sure this is worth it?

35:59.504 --> 36:03.868
I mean it's been like ten years
since you last saw her.

36:06.177 --> 36:07.798
Yeah... it's worth it.

36:11.915 --> 36:14.021
<font color="#D900D9">(EVAPORATING SOUND)</font>

36:45.504 --> 36:46.605
<font color="#808080">BOB:</font> It's amazing!

36:46.705 --> 36:48.356
The ma... The man with no hair!

36:48.782 --> 36:50.095
I can't believe it!

36:50.462 --> 36:52.568
<font color="#D900D9">(CATCHY TUNE, FUTURISTIC)</font>

36:52.935 --> 36:54.302
<font color="#808080">PA VOICE:</font> <i> <font color="#D900D9">(INAUDIBLE)</font></i>

37:01.027 --> 37:02.258
<font color="#D900D9">(INVERSE-METAL CLONKING)</font>

37:02.897 --> 37:04.553
So what kind of shirt you want?

37:04.653 --> 37:06.588
- You want like a sport shirt?<font color="#808080">
ADAM:</font> - No, no...

37:06.688 --> 37:08.883
T-shirt?
One of of the button-down collars?

37:08.983 --> 37:10.681
- Yes, like a normal button-down shirt.<font color="#808080">
BOB:</font> - You want a jacket?

37:11.025 --> 37:13.214
Yeah, like... I don't know...
a suit jacket.

37:14.858 --> 37:16.258
<font color="#D900D9">(INVERSE-METAL IN SUITCASE
CLONKING)</font>

37:17.379 --> 37:19.828
<font color="#D900D9">(CATCHY,
FUTURISTIC TUNE CONTINUES)</font>

37:20.433 --> 37:22.172
<font color="#808080">PA VOICE:</font> <i> Stay in line...</i>

37:27.069 --> 37:28.140
<font color="#D900D9">(METAL CLONKING)</font>

38:01.569 --> 38:03.995
<font color="#D900D9">(MUSIC FADING OUT)</font>

38:15.548 --> 38:16.855
<font color="#D900D9">(DOG SOFTLY GRUMBLING)</font>

38:17.151 --> 38:19.433
You may proceed, Mr. Kirk.

38:20.389 --> 38:21.389
Thank you.

38:22.073 --> 38:25.232
<font color="#D900D9">(SLIGHTLY SUSPENSEFUL VIOLIN TUNE)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(PLASTIC GLOVES STRETCHING)</font>

38:26.167 --> 38:29.941
<font color="#D900D9">(DOG MAKING DROOLING NOISE,
THEN GRUMBLING)</font>

38:31.195 --> 38:33.301
<font color="#D900D9">(DOG PANTING)</font>

38:36.425 --> 38:39.737
Now, this should be happening
any moment now.

38:41.477 --> 38:42.861
<font color="#808080">SCIENTIST:</font> You watch carefully.

38:43.772 --> 38:45.298
Here it comes.

38:48.824 --> 38:50.847
How long does the effect last?

38:51.581 --> 38:54.148
Well, right now really
only like a few minutes...

38:54.248 --> 38:55.609
...but I...
we've been working on...

38:55.633 --> 38:56.858
<font color="#808080">SCIENTIST:</font> It's been working
long enough.

38:56.964 --> 38:59.172
Soon we'll begin clinical trials
on human subjects.

38:59.555 --> 39:02.833
Obviously, we start with a sample
of women from down below.

39:02.939 --> 39:05.128
I need quick results.
I'm counting on you.

39:05.412 --> 39:06.630
<font color="#D900D9">(LUNCHTIME BUZZER)</font>

39:06.730 --> 39:08.263
<font color="#808080">EMPLOYEE 1:</font> Is that beauty cream
for Halloween?

39:08.488 --> 39:11.172
<font color="#808080">EMPLOYEE 2:</font> No, they got different
standards of beauty down below.

39:11.730 --> 39:14.877
The... uglier the better.
<font color="#D900D9">(BOTH CACKLING)</font>

39:16.758 --> 39:19.349
<font color="#808080">BOB:</font> Hey, don't let those guys
get to you.

39:19.787 --> 39:21.787
They're just jealous,
that's all.

39:22.130 --> 39:24.969
Are you... staying late?

39:25.069 --> 39:28.223
Yeah, you know, I thought I stay and
finish up a few things, you know.

39:28.323 --> 39:30.897
Ah, yeah. Well, I take the dog
back to the kennel.

39:31.215 --> 39:32.648
<font color="#808080">BOB:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(TO DOG)</font> Come on, girl.

39:32.748 --> 39:34.541
<font color="#808080">BOB:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(TO DOG)</font> Hey, here!

39:34.647 --> 39:37.179
<font color="#808080">BOB:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(TO ADAM)</font> You realize they don't pay
overtime, right?

39:37.279 --> 39:38.550
<font color="#808080">ADAM:</font> Yeah, I know.

39:38.650 --> 39:41.450
<font color="#808080">BOB:</font> Okay, alright.
See you tomorrow!

39:42.350 --> 39:43.864
<font color="#D900D9">(WITH SINGING VOICE)</font> Don't work too hard!

39:43.964 --> 39:45.237
<font color="#808080">ADAM:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(SMILING)</font> I won't.

39:46.952 --> 39:51.129
<font color="#D900D9">(SOFT TUNE FADING IN)</font>

39:52.507 --> 39:55.069
<font color="#D900D9">(TELEPHONE RINGING)</font>

39:59.198 --> 40:00.198
Hello?

40:00.913 --> 40:01.978
Yes, it is.

40:03.078 --> 40:05.196
No, I'm sorry,
she's got home for tonight.

40:06.723 --> 40:08.190
Yeah, you can come by tomorrow.

40:09.006 --> 40:10.875
Okay, what's your name again?

40:11.136 --> 40:14.117
BO-RU-CHOWITZ.

